					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=571081&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252576" alt="qntm" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=571081)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;" >qntm</a></span> <span class="odate time_1591458375 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 Jun 2020 15:46</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4678982">
									

<p>Unimaginable thanks to Rimple for editorial services on this chapter. This one was developed offline so I have never actually seen it with its full and proper formatting, a weird scenario for me.</p>
<p>About halfway through writing this I realised that to completely wrap everything up here would be far too rushed and sudden, as well as making the chapter too long. Pacing is difficult in prose. So, an epilogue will follow in approximately one week. Forcing everybody to sit and think about what they just read for a while seems like a strong choice here.</p>
<p>It was difficult to get started on this chapter because the brief was so simple that I couldn't figure out a way to make it interesting. &quot;Adam finds Bart Hughes; Hughes needs an idea to amplify, but Adam doesn't have it; so they recover Adam's memory of Marion and amplify that&quot; is three simple sentences. You kind of already know at least one and a half of them before even getting to this chapter. So that took some work. Turning Hughes <em>into</em> the machine I think helped a lot. As for the rest, well, the barbecue scene was hard to write, and the reunion too, but I absolutely love cosmic fight scenes.</p>
<p>Alternate titles: &quot;Freedom Means No Fear&quot; (Nina Simone quote), &quot;I Remember Nothing&quot;, &quot;We Were Strangers&quot;, &quot;Uncontainable&quot;, &quot;The Universe Where We Win&quot; (oops, spoilers), &quot;Sleep Furiously&quot;, &quot;Our Marion&quot;, &quot;This Needs To Be The End&quot; (sounds like an authorial whine), &quot;Apollyon&quot;, &quot;[DATA EXPUNGED]&quot; (it's been done), &quot;[REDACTED]&quot; (also done), &quot;███████████████████&quot; (bad SEO, and what does it stand for?) and many others.</p>

							</div>

								
					
