			<div class="content" id="post-content-4679051">
									

<p>Simply Incredible. On series-wide scale, You did a wonderful job handling the slow transition from Marion's gritty, earthly beginnings in Site-41, to the ideatic ghosts of Omega-0, to the surreal hell of a 3125-infested world, and finally to the cosmic sci-fi of Tombstone. Successfully managing that kind of escalation in setting while staying true to the story's original tone and characters is a feat few authors have accomplished, bravo. +1</p>

