																		Incredible
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lunardelta" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2898811); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2898811&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252576" alt="LunarDelta" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2898811)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lunardelta" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2898811); return false;" >LunarDelta</a></span> <span class="odate time_1591471627 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 Jun 2020 19:27</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4679111">
									

<p>The ending almost brought a tear to my eye. Go Marion! And Adam! And Hughes! The description of Marion's idea complex as a &quot;WILD LIGHT&quot; fighting against something that is made of wrongness and profound, self-consistent evil reminded me of the ending of the video game &quot;Okami&quot; where Amaterasu battles the &quot;Emperor of Everlasting Darkness&quot;. In particular, this song, &quot;The Sun Rises&quot; <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ya3yxTbkh5s">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ya3yxTbkh5s</a></p>
<p>It's beautiful, brilliant like the sun. It's triumphant. It's the kind of song that plays when you <em>know</em> victory is assured and the battle ahead is just a formality. I can just imagine this playing as she spreads her wings and achieves &quot;ignition&quot;, blasting off into ideatic space to put an end to the insanity once and for all.</p>
<p>&quot;She looks at him, and at herself, and at their fictional little scene, steadily brightening as the Sun rises.&quot;</p>
<p>You know, come to think of it, &quot;The Sun Rises&quot; would have been a cool name for the chapter, because really, the sun <em>did</em> rise on multiple levels. The conceptual sun of WILD LIGHT obliterating the darkness of 3125, and the real sun finally rising now that the false, evil red sun of 3125 is gone.</p>

							</div>

								
