														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4679161">
									

<p>What can I even say? Your concept, your story is magnificent. An idea of evil thought by something so much larger than humans that the idea scalds reality itself. The simple, harsh way you elidicate the horror that Adam experienced, never once specifying anything but still painting something ugly, wrong, worse. The melancholy realisation at the end of how much this thing has cut and eaten away from them, the bittersweetness of a final reunion where the only real gift is knowing how much they lost. The way you conceptualise the abstract, how it connects to the real, how it connects to the irreal, and how the fight is an elegant refutation, the rejection of an awful universe in favour of one where love can transcend, here in the most literal possible ways.</p>
<p>This is, quite literally, the best writing on this site. I look forward, and fear, what will be left of humanity after this, and how much they will remember of what they did.</p>

							</div>

								
					
