			<div class="content" id="post-content-4679162">
									

<p>What a profoundly satisfying ending to this story.<br />
God DAMN I love a good cosmic fight scene.</p>
<p>Every part of this gave me that horrible feeling, an undeniably true but deeply disgusting combination of the distinctly human and the totally alien. The description of Hughes' body genuinely made me nauseous, especially as someone who can take some meaning out of the word &quot;dysmorphia&quot;. And there's this almost mythical tone, everyone here being elevated beyond characters and into archetypes. Very fitting considering the battle takes place in a world of ideas rather than flesh. It's genius, brilliant, I love it.</p>

