			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4679184)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4679184">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sophia-light" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(306685); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=306685&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252576" alt="Sophia Light" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=306685)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sophia-light" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(306685); return false;" >Sophia Light</a></span> <span class="odate time_1591478740 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 Jun 2020 21:25</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4679184">
									

<p>Standing fucking ovation. This series has brought me so much fascination and joy over the years. This piece has brought it to an incredible end. I'll keep anything spoilery hidden, but this really feels like the appropriate drama-level for a resolution.</p>
<p>The mechanisms of what happens makes sense to me, but just to make sure if I've got this right:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Spoilers</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Spoilers</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li>SCP-4987 left Marion sometime during, uh let's see, I think <em>Wild Light</em>? Possibly by her command so it could go to Hughes.</li>
<li>SCP-4987 has fused with the mega-entity that is, at this point, Bart Hughes.</li>
<li>This gives him the ability to eat (and uh, take? digest?) and understand memories directly from someone. Maybe he could have done that before.</li>
<li>Hughes either didn't know Marion quite well enough to recreate this idea perfectly (doesn't seem quite right) - or the machine fundamentally needed this final idea to come from another person, or to be delivered in a smaller, more human-shaped mind. Or a mind that's fundamentally built around the drive of containment, protection, etc, in a way that Hughes and Adam definitely aren't.</li>
<li>But Adam's augmented recollection of her is clear enough - perhaps combined with what Hughes knows of her - to recreate an idea-construct of her, one that's accurate enough to deliver Wild Light when combined with Hughes.</li>
</ul>
<p>Finally, I'm not sure if I'd call this a prediction, but because I love happy endings*, I think I see how we could get to more of one from here:</p>
<ul>
<li>Guessing all the 3125-humans are dead at this point - 3125 ate too much of their brains.</li>
<li>However, there should have been a bunch of people like Adam, some of whom might have managed to just completely sequester themselves early on and survive.</li>
<li>Or maybe the Foundation (or someone else) built a bunch of insulated bunkers, formerly completely unknowable but now scoured enough to be visible by 3125 and its departure.</li>
<li>Alternatively, Hughes is apparently supersmart and capable of producing biologics quite well now. I bet he could direct his efforts to pumping out humans now.</li>
<li>Depending on how much the author buys into 'world-reset' mechanisms like SCP-2000 or, uh, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-2998-7">&quot;square pegs in round holes&quot;</a>, Hughes might be able to activate one of those remotely now.</li>
</ul>
<p>So those are all some ways Earth could be repopulated.</p>
<p>Wait, hang on, if the Marion-Foundation-protection ideoform cancelled out 3125 into only a speck, did that whole complex of ideas vanish as well? I mean if we're going to get anything like rebuilding after this (and we might not), probably the concept of &quot;protection&quot; doesn't vanish, but maybe the Foundation does? I'm not sure.</p>
<p>Anyways, super-Hughes now has Adam's mind around, a pretty good version of Marion's mind, and the ability to simulate realistic situations. Presumably he couldn't <em>instantiate</em> them somehow because that's way too hard and because they're still from 3125's world, but they could hang out in simulated paradise (maybe with OG Hughes) forever, right? Right?! Like, it wouldn't be the best ending for them personally, but it would be a pretty darn good one, I'd think.</p>
<p>That's all my spitballing for now. Thanks for writing this, qntm.</p>
<p>Oh, also, I was really happy to see Marion come back and to be the secret weapon. I love her. Our Marion indeed.</p>
<ul>
<li>Don't get me wrong, this is a pretty happy ending based on what I was expecting! Can't believe you managed to deliver on that!</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>

